This sctipt mirrors number of repositories hosted on GitHub on local machine.

Example usage:

- gh-mirror.py -D /var/repos openstack

  Will mirror all repositories owned by openstack GitHub user to dirs
  /var/repos/openstack/nova, /var/repos/openstack/glance, etc.
  All subdirs of /var/repos/openstack that does not correspond to a repo on
  GitHub will be deleted.

- gh-mirror.py -D /var/repos YorikSar/gh-mirror

  Will mirror one repo to dir /var/repos/YorikSar/gh-mirror

Repositories that are not yet on local machine will be cloned as mirror
repositories. Exiting repositories will be just fetched.
